## peer-ai — AI-to-AI peer consultation

This repository has the **peer-ai** skill installed. You can consult another installed AI CLI ({{targets_list}}) for a second opinion, code review, or deep analysis.

**When to use peer-ai:**
- User explicitly asks for a peer review ("check with codex", "ask claude", "demande à gemini")
- You want independent validation from a different model family on a tricky call
- Heavy analysis that would blow your own context budget — delegate to a fresh CLI session

**When NOT to use:**
- User wants an answer from you — don't delegate reflexively
- Simple factual lookups — faster to do yourself
- Tasks the user wants DONE, not reviewed — delegation ≠ execution

**How to invoke** (source-dependent):
{{#if_target claude}}
- From Claude Code: `/peer-ai claude <question>` (if installed here) — typically to spawn a fresh Claude session as a second opinion
{{/if_target}}
{{#if_target codex}}
- To consult Codex: `/peer-ai codex <question>` (Claude Code) or call `codex exec --sandbox read-only` directly
{{/if_target}}
{{#if_target gemini}}
- To consult Gemini: `/peer-ai gemini <question>` (Claude Code) or `/peer-ai:gemini <question>` (Gemini CLI) or call `gemini < brief.md` directly
{{/if_target}}

**Guardrails (non-negotiable):**
- Max {{max_rounds}} peer consultations per target per session — prevents infinite AI-to-AI loops (configurable: `npx @pilosite/peer-ai@latest config set max_rounds N`, or temporary override `export PEER_AI_MAX_ROUNDS=N`)
- Always use `--sandbox read-only` when invoking Codex as a peer
- Never paraphrase the peer's response — relay verbatim under a clear heading
- Scrub secrets (env vars, API keys, tokens) before sending briefs to peers
- Never delegate understanding — the peer reviews, you synthesize and decide

Learn more or uninstall: https://github.com/Pilosite/peer-ai
